# React Rules

Build React and Next.js code that is clear, composed, and aligned with the existing app.

## Components

- Keep components focused on one responsibility.
- Extract components when it reduces real complexity or matches an existing local pattern.
- Prefer explicit props and stable data flow.
- Keep server/client boundaries intentional in Next.js.

## State

- Model UI states explicitly: loading, empty, error, active, disabled, dragging, selected.
- Keep drag and node interactions predictable.
- Avoid hidden global state unless the feature truly needs shared coordination.

## Accessibility

- Make controls keyboard reachable.
- Use semantic elements where practical.
- Preserve focus states and visible interaction feedback.
